The provocation of a yellow card under such or similar circumstances is not a new practice, it is more likely to occur in the world of football.
It is so widespread that it is part of the ethos - the unwritten but followed rules in this sport.
Part of the debate about the case presented is that a team of Real Madrid football club (who in his anthem pretended to be noble and honour and had punished his players on other occasions for similar incidents) played the main role, provoking as the protagonist, and on the dramatization of the story by a more epic of the Mourinho.
In any case, the debate is about whether this is not explicitly contrary to the principles of sport prohibited by the statutes, that is, whether these acts constitute a violation of the rules. In fact, this approach adheres to the statutes of the sport, but seems to be inconsistent with its meaning.
In this case, the damage caused to the sporting spirit should be investigated.
The sporting spirit defends the physical integrity of the opponents, an aspect that was not endangered by these actions, because it was not an aggressive game.
Another aspect of a clean game is to avoid the opposing players taking an unjustified benefit from the opposing team.
The paradox of Real Madrid players’ actions is that they do not correspond to what we normally understand by misplay or rule-making, because circumvention of the rule was not secretly carried out in order to avoid a penalty, but it should be as noticeable as possible so that it is punished by the referee.
