It is not clear if this is really an advantage.
Ultimately, such approaches are not directed against the sporting spirit, which also includes strategic decisions to make the most of the rules.
In this case, the players did not want to circumvent a sanction (this would actually be a clear case of regulatory breach), they wanted to choose when to submit to it.
They made a strategic decision without escaping or escaping from a punishment.
Although the boundary between giving of the invention and the regulatory environment is obscured, I believe that this is a clear case of giving of the invention.
